		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Glasshoppa&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>By far, at least where I've hunted, the majority of mobs are beating you physically and not with spells. You'd be much better served finding items with increased HP/AC and AGI followed by STA, STR, and then DEX. Resistances after that.<br><br>I might put some effort into keeping a higher Magic Resistance to avoid the roots and blindness spells. Other than that all the spells you are hoping to avoid are damage related. If you have items that increase your HP's it aids you in both physical and magical attacks.<br><br>AGI helps make you harder to hit in melee as well as reducing the amount of damage you take when you are hit. I made this the first priority with my Monk. In fact, in the bazaar, Wu's gear that was 40-50pp pre-bazaar can now be had for 15-20. Not what I would call expensive. The Drolvarg Mantle is also a steal and can be had for around 40-50pp.<br><br>I'm at level 22 now and have done just fine without increased resistance gear. Sure it could help but not nearly as beneficial as other gear.<br><br>EDIT: I am 64 now and while the above statement was true at lower levels, at higher levels resists become extremely important. I solo'd a lot up through level 50 or so AC/HP was key but soling just isn't very practical anymore. As a monk your job is often to pull and being able to resist spells from casters you are pulling is awfully nice and of course AoE spells on bosses/raids. I now carry many resist items to swap out for stat items as the situation dictates.<br><br><i><span class=sm>Edited, Mon Jun 14 17:59:14 2004 by Glasshoppa</span class=sm></i></p><s